title: Texas Attorney General Ken Paxton acquitted in impeachment trial
description: Paxton was impeached for allegedly taking bribes, but ultimately members of his party chose not to vote for his conviction and removal from office.

title: Russell Brand denies sexual assault allegations against him
description: British comedian and actor Russell Brand is denying allegations of sexual assault against him published as a result of a joint investigation published Saturday by the Times of London, The Sunday Times and Channel 4 Dispatches.

title: Striking autoworkers want to end a system that pays different wages for the same job
description: Striking auto workers want to be paid more equally, setting their sights on a staggered wage system that they say is unfair.

title: Storm Lee now a post-tropical cyclone; expected to make landfall in eastern Canada
description: Post-tropical cyclone Lee is gearing up to make landfall in Nova Scotia in eastern Canada Saturday.

title: Sen. Fetterman to walk picket line in Michigan as UAW strike enters second day
description: Sen. Fetterman to walk picket line in Michigan as UAW strike enters second day

title: How effective are credit monitoring services?
description: It’s an email now familiar to millions of Americans: A company was hit by a cyberattack, resulting in the leak of personal information.

title: Biden allies worry Hunter’s indictment could strain the president’s 2024 focus
description: People close to the president are increasingly concerned about how Hunter Biden's indictment could divide his attention when he needs to be focused on 2024.

title: Expected CDC guidance on N95 masks outrages health care workers
description: Do N95 masks work better than surgical masks? A draft proposal from the CDC suggests the two are equivalent in certain hospital settings.

title: Trump says he likes 'the concept' of a female VP pick
description: Former President Donald Trump said he likes "the concept" of choosing a woman to be his vice presidential pick.

title: Democrats in Ohio say they’ll need a new recipe for a second huge abortion rights win
description: Abortion rights activists shocked themselves and the Ohio political world when they resoundingly defeated an August proposal that would have made it more difficult to enshrine abortion protections in the state’s constitution.

title: Iran's protests have been crushed, but Mahsa Amini’s death is still felt a year later around the world
description: A year after her death, thousands of people across the world are expected to march in memory of Mahsa Amini — but Iranian authorities have worked to ensure that there will not be a repeat of the demonstrations that swept the country last year.
